The paper deals with the design of Plug-and-Play controllers for AC Islanded microGrids (ImGs), which involves the use of control theory and power systems engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses network reduction methods and their application to ImGs, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Additionally, the paper involves the design of controllers for power systems, which could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
